# Shell scripts MUST use LF endings — they run inside Linux containers (e.g. the feature-026
# mc-service/mongo-entrypoint.sh, opensearch/init-audit-user.sh). A CRLF shebang/line makes the
# container fail with "bad interpreter" / "\r" errors. Force LF regardless of a contributor's
# core.autocrlf on Windows.
*.sh text eol=lf
